Bottle from aldi. Lovely combo if hops. Expect more head and carbonation a little flat and watery but nice beer overall
Burnt roasty. Flat as a witches tit nothing to write home about. But tasty still. Dear
bottle from goose offy. very nice for the pilsner style. strong malt taste little hops for style. nicely carbonated much better then other lagers ive had
Bottle from artane. Very light and straw very watery better then the well known na largers would drink again
Bottle from martins. Rocky head lots of banna and clove. Easy drinker for sure prop my fav na

Can from Monaghan. Nice earthy hops, fuggle ect. Slight malt bacbone and good carbonation. Nicer cold a well. Better then shitwicks by a country mile. Would return for more if I was a raging alcoholic
Can from londis ballybofey, vile dishwater of epic proportions, Id rather lick puke then drink this again
Bottle from clondalkin, think the bottle was brown.  little carbonation,watery finish have had better Weiss in my time
Bottle from clondalkin, very nice dunkel Weiss. Small head well rounded and sweet with bannana
Bottle from sainsburys derry.deep hello pour citrus and grassy on the nose with orange. Caramel butterscotch too. Very tasty I pa slight bitterness well balanced, hard to beat

Bottle from sansburys. Dark amber on the pour. Little to no head. Malty on the nose. Reminds me of paulaner octoberfest, bready and caramelly. Obviously Vienna and/or Munich used. Little bittering and hops well rounded. Decent lager for sure

Bottle from asda. Lovely colour small head little head.. caramel. Bread and chocolate. . Watery finish but rolls off the tongue.  Some sugar spice used here too. Nutty taste.Its all about the brewing liquor used in this I suspect hard, Burton water. Very decent brown from why I?ve had of them.

Bottle from as a. Love the challanger hops in this. Seems to be chock full of aroma hopping spruce and citrus on the nose.Lovely rich golden colour. Not much carbonation on the bottle or head or lacing. A nice finished beer but not something I?d enjoy drinking all the time
Bottle from as a srabane. Malty smell and taste, light hoping in bittering. Defo crystal notes. Very well balanced indeed. Drank at room temp. More carbonation then normal for an ale.
Bought in bottle from lidl Spain. Very nice. Enjoyed them dark and ready will be having them again
Bottle from the apartment Belfast. OK nothing to write home about lager. Enjoyed a here afterwards which was much nicer then I?d remembered. This lager is a nothing special.
Bottle in almeria. Nice ban a notes very good, enjoyed this similar to weinstephen. Would be back
Bottle from lidl almeria. Nice abbey here. Similar to leffe brune. Nice tan head lots of spice and aroma. Would drink again
Bottle from Mercado a almeria. Very bland but pleasant to drink. Nice carbonation. Good for a thirst quencher thats about it
Bottle from mecadonna almeria. Too strong of an ale for what it is, trying too hard with this. Awful
Bottle Chinese restaurant, quite pleasant always liked it really its refreshing with a curry
Bottle Russian shop almeria, boring saazy lager here no aroma, generally poor like most Generic
Bottle in Russian shop in almeria? using maltose syrup was decent enough, pretty sweet

Enjoyed a pint in oasis letterkenny followed after a full strength which not having had one for awhile tasted pretty bland and mediocre, so the mid strength that followed was pretty much the same in my book, but nice to have a pint without getting buzzed too quick you could pace yourself with a few of these in between, would go back for more
Bottle from dunnes, nice crisp tight head lots of chocolate and crisp carbonation the way an extra is suppose to be, nice would like to test against the guiness extra

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: bottle from derrys german market was the tap 7 unser original bottle  which comes under this same one. darker amber colour. to be fair I had this after a hooegarden which is a lot different then this original but overall it was an average hefe I felt.

Bottle from tesco. sweet honey and biscuity/malty on the nose from the vienna. super clear filtered weiss beer which I wasnt expecting.very little bittering. but overall a little sweet for my liking but still a lovely beer and very different then the erdinger which is not tru to style and is a mix between a hefe and pills, supposedly this more like a helles and I tend to agree with that, need to try more

bottle from tesco. my first Oktoberfestbier and very nice. although erdinger which is not tru to style and is a mix between a hefe and pills is reallly good regardless. cloudy slight citrus and spice nothing too powerful. delicious till the end.
bottle from tescos. decent hefe nothing standout. head lasting longer then frank. think the paulner could be the nicest and more complex hefe around. yet to try others . this is not a bad hefeweizen.

BOTTLE FROM ASDA. Roasty and chocolatey obvious real chocolate used and maybe candy sugar, have saved the yeast for later. overall a litttle heavy and not session able like most say. but different with spices and adjuncts the whitewater brewery is and has a made a name for itself because of it.
UPDATED: DEC 6, 2012
Bottle from lidl. not a lot to say other then drinkable. its got nothing going for it besides that
bottle from eurospar. nice cider. better then bulmers . need to wrk on my cider palette
bottle from eurospar in gorthahork. nice aftertaste clean and refreshing. decent stuff for a nice helles beer

bottle from asda 5.2. toffee nose. roast and choc malts slight citrus hop with a dry finish. not bad .....not really had many porters to compare in fairness

Bottled at 4.7% from tesco letterkenny. lovely carbonation and great colour. nice head retention. good bittering and aroma. a lovely ale indeed.
500ml bottle from gormelys centra. sweet honey piss no thanks never again shall I partake in this crap
Pint from the diamond in derry. malted base. no head. flat. rough crowd. but will be back to sample more beers.ekg and first gold hops.
Bottle from harrys bridgend. rip off 5 euro. no co2 evident. enjoyable ale but not memorable.
